The paper discusses the challenges of developing systems with evolving requirements, which is a common concern in software engineering (cs.SE). The study from CERN focuses on handling descriptions of objects in practice alongside their instances, which suggests a database-related approach (cs.DB). The paper also mentions a "description-driven" approach, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL). The study's focus on facilitating dynamic system reconfiguration and responsive prototyping suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
